<% layout('layouts/infoBoilerplate') -%>

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-900 to-gray-800 pt-20 pb-16 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div
            class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full opacity-10 bg-[url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/cubes.png')]">
        </div>
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-4 tracking-tight">
                <i class="fas fa-calendar-times text-[#fe424d] mr-3"></i> Cancellation Policy
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Understanding our flexible and strict cancellation
                options for guests and hosts.</p>
            <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-gray-400 font-medium tracking-wider uppercase">Last updated: August 30, 2026</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12">

            <div class="lg:w-1/4 hidden lg:block">
                <div
                    class="sticky top-28 bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-3xl p-6 shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)]">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm flex items-center gap-2">
                        <i class="fas fa-list text-[#fe424d]"></i> Contents
                    </h3>
                    <nav class="sticky-nav flex flex-col space-y-1">
                        <a href="#guest-cancellation"
                            class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-transparent hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">Guest
                            Cancellations</a>
                        <a href="#host-cancellation"
                            class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-transparent hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">Host
                            Cancellations</a>
                        <a href="#refunds"
                            class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-transparent hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">Refund
                            Processing</a>
                        <a href="#extenuating"
                            class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-transparent hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">Extenuating
                            Circumstances</a>
                    </nav>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="lg:w-3/4 prose-content bg-white p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)] border border-gray-100">

                <div id="guest-cancellation">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-suitcase-rolling"></i> Guest Cancellations</h2>
                    <p>Hosts on Stayzio can choose from several standardized cancellation policies that we will enforce
                        to protect both guests and hosts.</p>

                    <div class="highlight-box">
                        <h4><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Flexible Policy</h4>
                        <p>Guests can cancel up to 24 hours before check-in for a full refund, and you won't be charged
                            for the stay.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mt-8 border-l-4 border-gray-200 pl-6 py-2">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 text-lg mb-2">Moderate Policy</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-600">Guests must cancel at least 5 days before check-in to receive a full
                            refund.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mt-6 border-l-4 border-red-200 pl-6 py-2">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 text-lg mb-2">Strict Policy</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-600">To receive a full refund, guests must cancel within 48 hours of
                            booking, and the cancellation must occur at least 14 days before check-in.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="host-cancellation">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-home"></i> Host Cancellations</h2>
                    <p>Because cancellations disrupt guests' plans and impact confidence in the Stayzio community, hosts
                        should fulfill all confirmed reservations. However, we understand that extenuating circumstances
                        arise.</p>
                    <p>If a host cancels, guests will receive a full and immediate refund. We also offer automated
                        assistance to help the guest find another place to stay.</p>
                </div>

                <div id="refunds">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-money-bill-wave"></i> Refund Processing</h2>
                    <p>Refunds are processed automatically when a reservation is cancelled. The amount refunded depends
                        on the host's cancellation policy and the time of cancellation.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Most refunds arrive within 3-5 business days.</li>
                        <li>Refunds are sent to the original payment method used during booking.</li>
                        <li>Stayzio service fees are non-refundable in cases of strict policy violations.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div id="extenuating">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-cloud-showers-heavy"></i> Extenuating Circumstances</h2>
                    <p>In rare instances, emergencies or severe circumstances may prevent you from completing a trip or
                        hosting a guest. Under our Extenuating Circumstances Policy, you might be eligible for a refund
                        (for guests) or waiver of cancellation penalties (for hosts).</p>
                    <p>Covered circumstances include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Declared emergencies and epidemics.</li>
                        <li>Government travel restrictions.</li>
                        <li>Natural disasters affecting the destination.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>